HEADWORD: Pickaxe
<hw>Pick"axe`</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(p⟦icr⟧k"⟦acr⟧ks`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A corruption of OE.
<ets>pikois</ets>, <ets>pikeis</ets>, F. <ets>picois</ets>, fr.
<ets>pic</ets>. See <er>Pick</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>A pick with
a point at one end, a transverse edge or blade at the other, and a
handle inserted at the middle; a hammer with a flattened end for driving
wedges and a pointed end for piercing as it strikes.</def>
